				\begin{document}$\sim1.56~\text{m}$\end{document}. There are two autofocus methods (AF): the image-based autofocus (RMI-AF) can be used at any distance, while the laser-based autofocus (CWL-AF) is limited to distances of less than 7 m

To benefit from a ±180∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
