				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$>30$\end{document} optical parts (Table 5), most of which are custom made. The primary mirror is the most distinctive piece of the design (Fig. 43, optics #1). Largely inherited from ChemCam, the extruded structure is made of aluminum (see next section, last paragraph). The optical surface shape error is 17 nm rms, and roughness is ∼4.5nm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
