The RF generation circuit locks the Voltage Controlled Oscillators (VCO) at a selected frequency between 33.1 MHz to 67.8 MHz. A controllable gain controls the first stage of amplification. The VCO can be disabled to switch the RF signal off. The performance of the clock oscillator allows the stability of the RF signal to be better than ±10kHz\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
