				\begin{document}$+35~^{\circ }\text{C}$\end{document}, and distances between 2 m and 7 m. They help to redefine some use cases, for the margins to the laser relaxed mode for instance. Results are presented all through with this publication.

The IR range is new and includes several challenges, not so much the collection of light, but its spectral dispersion. AOTFs are not new in space but they are delicate to drive, in particular when the two diffracted orders are recorded and need to be angularly stabilized; additionally, the commercial IR photodiodes were difficult to qualify, which is one reason for designing the instrument with redundant sensors. The electromagnetic environment of these photodiodes has been treated with the utmost care to obtain an electronic noise <0.1pA\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$<0.1~\text{pA}$\end{document}.

